Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.32,0:06:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its meaning at the time.\NUh,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.36,0:06:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these I can't quite make out the\Nthe meaning of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.80,0:06:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nwhat would Mother Teresa have said in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.24,0:06:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Bash's parking lot?\NMother Teresa,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.96,0:06:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I don't speak Hindi.\NShe probably would have said
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I blessed you my brother.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.68,0:06:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> huh.\N>> You understand Mother Teresa? We'll
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.96,0:06:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,understand her next month. Next month\Nwe'll be more than mother Teresa because
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.12,0:06:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,next\Ntalk is the way to god through devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.03,0:06:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,through the heart to you know most of\Nthese lectures we've been approaching it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.47,0:07:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,more like the zen more like um\Nnonduality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,vita or advita whatever you call it\Nuh I how do you pronounce it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.44,0:07:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> adva\Nlike the pickle herring advita
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.88,0:07:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,edit pickle tearing, right? Yeah.\NAll right. So, we've been dissecting the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,mind, taking it apart, and uh one of the\Nreasons we did it in this sequence is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because when the obstacles to love are\Nremoved,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.19,0:07:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it it's sudden. The way the sudden\Nenlightenment is you remove all the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,obstacles and then you turn up the fire\Nunder the burner and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.19,0:07:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so everybody be enlightened within 60\Ndays.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.16,0:07:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We've tried to do it in that way. I\Nnoticed that the course of miracles did
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.52,0:07:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it the same way. I was fascinated by the\Ncourse of miracles because before
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.68,0:08:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting you with the truth that I am\Nlove and I am spirit and God and I are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.87,0:08:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,one etc. Long before that it first\Ndisassembles the ego. First it takes the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.36,0:08:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,ego out which is going to say this is\Nnonsense. This wouldn't apply to me. I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.87,0:08:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just a nobody. First it says, you know,\Nmy thoughts don't mean anything. Whoa,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a brilliant move. When I saw\Nthat lesson, I said, this is spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.40,0:08:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,genius. This is written by spiritual\Ngenius to see that the sequence should
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.40,0:08:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,be to first disassemble the ego before\Nyou present it with spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.00,0:08:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion does it the other way. Presents\Nyou with spiritual truth at a point
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,where you couldn't possibly grasp that\Nthat's a reality. You got so much guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.44,0:08:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn't own that for yourself. You\Ngot so much shame you couldn't possibly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.32,0:08:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,do it. You got so much annoyance at God\Nwho's going to punish you later and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're so scared of him, you hate him.\NReligion doesn't have a chance with the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.76,0:08:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,average person. You know, you got to\Ntalk yourself into believing it. And
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.48,0:08:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what's called faith\Ndespite all the irrationality of it. You
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.88,0:09:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,know, you go with it.\NBut for a spiritual seeker, then the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.64,0:09:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,correct sequence is to first comprehend\Nthe nature of the ego. How it got to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that way so that you can own it. You\Ncan't own the ego if you're going to go
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,into guilt, shame, see it as your enemy,\Nhate it, fear it, etc. And some
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.92,0:09:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual pathways do that. They set up\Nthe ego as an enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and reinforce it.\NSo by familiarity, we we we take the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.44,0:09:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,apart, you know, stick by stick like\Npickup sticks. We see how it does. This
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.24,0:09:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,creates a bifurcation. Then we go back\Nto the source of the bifurcation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.12,0:09:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You surrender that the bifurcation, all\Nthe multiple bifurcations that come off
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.04,0:09:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of that decision now all disappear.\NAll the algorithms, you know, one choice
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.92,0:09:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,creates a duality. Each branch of the\Nduality now bifrocates until you've got
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.88,0:09:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands and thousands of your neurons\Nall jumping with hate in the bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:10:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then loud and you want to kill him. He's\Nawful. He's evil. He's terrible. He's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.24,0:10:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,see all that stuff.\NThe guy doesn't know what he's doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.00,0:10:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,does he? He's a mental case, right?\Nto be brainwashed into the exact
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite of the spiritual truth, there's\Ngot to be a few nuts and bolts missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.12,0:10:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NAll right. So, if we disassemble the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by understanding its structure, so if\Nyou want to take something apart, you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.92,0:10:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,understand how it's put together. If you\Nunderstand how it put is put together,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.83,0:10:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,now you can start taking the sticks out\Nand the structure becomes weaker and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.07,0:10:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,weaker, weaker and weaker. Then you come\Nin with the fire of the heart. after all
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.83,0:10:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the obstacles have been removed, it\Nwould have already eliminated it or
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.83,0:10:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,deterred you from even following the\Npathway of devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the sequence of the lectures we\Nstarted with
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.76,0:10:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic underpinning of the ego which\Nis the belief in causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.64,0:10:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We worked our way through how dualistic\Nthinking arises and how to let go of the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.56,0:11:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,positionality because it only creates a\Nwhole another set of dualities each
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.64,0:11:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,branch of which present creates a whole\Nanother set of dualities and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,pull the pin on the whole bank of it.\NSee millions of neurons and then you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.83,0:11:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,pull the pin on this one they go silent.\NAll that chitchat stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.76,0:11:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the reason we've presented\Nthis
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.04,0:11:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in the sequence that it has. So this is\Nnumber eight. And I think the way of the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.60,0:11:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,heart is number nine.\NAnd having seen that the obstacles were
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.88,0:11:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,all artifacts of mentalization with no\Nintrinsic reality, we can easily
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.95,0:11:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,dispense with them.\NIn that point, at that point then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.83,0:11:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual commitment\Nuh intensity
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.76,0:11:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,um what it takes to break the 4-minute\Nmile now will have a chance to succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.60,0:11:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,without all those impediments in their\Nway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.20,0:12:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So first we tried to remove the\Nobstructions before return of the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.92,0:12:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the reason for the sequence of\Nthe of the lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.39,0:12:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start with you should be loving\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.20,0:12:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start with\Nas many religions do
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.80,0:12:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to love God, the heart of Jesus, the\Nstatues, the whole thing, you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.51,0:12:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,compelled\Nto love on a level which your ego will
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.32,0:12:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not allow you to love at.\NIf you could love it that degree, you'd
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.92,0:12:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,already be there. So it puts, it seems\Nto me that that is putting a cart in a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.20,0:12:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,horse before you pressure people to\Nbecome loving. You have to remove the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.80,0:12:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,obstructions without which they would\Nautomatically become loving because the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.27,0:13:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God within you expresses\Nitself as divinity expresses itself as
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.16,0:13:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,universal love. So we try to remove the\Nobstacles
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.27,0:13:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then lovingness becomes a real\Npossibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Too often it becomes an artificial\Nself-belief. I hear all kinds of people
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.60,0:13:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me how pious they are and how\Nloving they are. Yeah. Right. Till it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.12,0:13:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,comes to your mother, right?\NTill it comes to your mother-in-law,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.27,0:13:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your ex-wife. Right. The exception start\Ncoming up. So that degree of lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.72,0:13:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that on which is to uh arrive at is is\Nobstructed by the ego. So we're trying
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.00,0:13:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to disassemble the ego. All right. So\Nwhere is our calibrated levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.80,0:13:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness?\NSome spirit keeps whisking them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.51,0:13:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught him. There he is.\NThere you are, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.80,0:13:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was me all along. See what I mean?\NWhat's the point of trying to change the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.48,0:14:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,world and look for the chart thief when\Nhe's me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.95,0:14:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, intention. A lot of\Nspiritual work comes out of the solar
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.63,0:14:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,plexus.\NIt's ambition. Spiritual ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.36,0:14:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ambition. So, it's sort of a solar\Nplexus drive. You see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.24,0:14:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming out of the solar plexus. So\Na lot of driven kind of spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.63,0:14:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which some branches of some churches\Nover time you know displayed to severe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.00,0:14:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees are coming out of the solar\Nplexus got nothing to do with love. You
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,see and so you keep you know we we're\Ngoing to put you on the rack and keep it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.83,0:14:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,going until you agree to love God.\NIf the nature of the self with a capital
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.76,0:14:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,S within is not different than that\Nwhich is love, then to merely remove its
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.19,0:15:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,obstacles allows the love to shine\Nforth. The divinity of the self within
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is unmistakable. And as it shines forth,\Nit begins to radiate much like a much
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.24,0:15:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,like the dawn.\NAs you see, the decision to be loving is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.83,0:15:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a decision. It's a love. It's not within\Nthe realm of reason. This is logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic would tell you love that guy. He\Nshould be in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.32,0:15:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Love him. He's a criminal. I'm saying\Nreason would tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.39,0:15:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's ridiculous to love all these\Nways that you're supposed to love. And
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.80,0:15:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then you go to church and you're\Nsupposed to have a loving heart and love
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.76,0:15:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your neighbor as yourself. How can you\Nlove your neighbor as yourself when he's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.76,0:15:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,such a creep?\NSo you pretend he's not really a creep.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.92,0:16:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie. He is a creep.\NYou run him on the creep index.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.63,0:16:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a creep. Everybody in the\Nneighborhood thinks he's creep. He is a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.75,0:16:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,creep.\NReason says he is a creep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate him and I feel guilty about\Nhating him. I feel sad that he I feel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.44,0:16:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sad that he moved into my neighborhood\Nand I hate him so much I'm afraid that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.12,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,he may have retaliatory or homicidal\Nfantasies towards me which throws me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,into paranoia.\NHowever, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.51,0:16:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,out of courage I'm I'm pleased with\Nmyself that I faced up to him and told
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.16,0:16:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,him if you don't stop what my calling\NI'm going to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This throws me right back down to\Nparanoia again. I figure he's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.51,0:16:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, reason isn't too much of a help\Nright here. It keeps throwing us back
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.68,0:16:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and forth into this basket.\NAll right. So, the willingness to love
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.63,0:17:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what is a count. It's really a\Npact you're making with God. It's really
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.80,0:17:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a packact you're making with God.\NI choose to be with thy will, oh Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.64,0:17:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and love unconditionally.\NAll right? So, this is a choice made by
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.72,0:17:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious decision,\Nnot out of logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.43,0:17:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but because you're already evolved\Nenough
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.95,0:17:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that that contract is now compelling.\NCompelling. You realize it's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.55,0:17:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have a big cost. You realize it's going\Nto make a cost. Anybody who chooses to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.48,0:17:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,be unconditionally loving knows in that\Ncontract
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.79,0:17:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there's going to be a price.\NAll that which is unloving is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,come up to be surrendered.\NOn the other hand, you now get
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.91,0:17:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,assistance from dimensions from which\Nyou never got assistance before. Let's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.88,0:17:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,see if that's all.\NYou have permission to ask this
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:18:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,question. What I just said is so\Nsee contract is not now brought in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.48,0:18:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,powers from other dimensions which you\Ndid not have before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you're trying to become\Nunconditionally loving from down here in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.44,0:18:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego, you haven't got the power that\Nit takes to become unconditionally
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,loving. So you keep falling back into\Ndespair. And you see spiritual histories
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.08,0:18:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout time of various saints how\Nthey would go into high state then they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.60,0:18:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would fall.\NOh my beloved, how could you have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,deserted me?\NThey're in the presence of the bliss of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.08,0:18:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence. And then suddenly it\Ndisappears and they crash into severe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,dark knights of the soul.\NThe dark night of the soul is from
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.48,0:18:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to push the envelope. You're\Ntrying to push to unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.67,0:18:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when you haven't let go of what is\Nholding you back from unconditional
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.28,0:18:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,love.\NConsequently, I tell everybody, "Stop
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.44,0:19:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to be loving. Give me a break.\NWill you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.28,0:19:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,stop trying to be loving?\NYou're putting a pressure on me, on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.60,0:19:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on everybody.\NQuit trying to be loving. It either
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.16,0:19:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs of its own or it does not. In any\Nforce kind of love, it's going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.72,0:19:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,artificial. It's going to lack within it\Nthe security system. You see, because
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.08,0:19:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,love is going to lead you into dangerous\Nsituations. Without the help of unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,helpers, you're not going to be able to\Nhandle the seas at that. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.12,0:19:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to force yourself.\NBecause when the time is ready, it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.64,0:19:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes the way you are automatically.\NYou walk through the alley, the beetle
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.44,0:19:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is laying on his back. He needs help.\NYou either squish him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.79,0:20:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a shock to do that. You squish\Nhim or you say
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.16,0:20:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the last time I did it. The idiot\Nturned back on his back again. I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"Jesus, what's the matter with you?" I\Nput the twig on him again. He went over
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.76,0:20:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on his back again.\NI said, "There's some message here I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,not getting. I'm trying to exert my will\Non him and make him choose life. Sure
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.12,0:20:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,enough, when I came back in early, he\Nwas dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.28,0:20:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I turned my will to the Beatles will. He\Nwanted to leave this body and go get
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.36,0:20:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,himself a new body cuz the old one's all\Nworn out. You know what I mean? He
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.32,0:20:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,probably went over the other side,\Nreincarnated another and he's probably
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,back flying around already. Is he black\Nflying around already? Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.84,0:20:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this question.\NHe's back flying around already. By God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.91,0:20:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he is. I knew he was going to turn right\Naround, get reborn in an egg, and be out
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.28,0:20:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there flying again.\NSee, because you cannot kill life. Life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.76,0:21:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is not subject to death. That's one of\Nthe most profound things we said in all
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.91,0:21:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,these lectures.\NLife is not subject to death. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.48,0:21:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is not subject to death.\NSomething of its own quality. It takes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.79,0:21:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,something of its own power, its own\Nquality to kill it. Nothing has the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,power to kill life.\NYou cannot kill anything. You cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.79,0:21:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,kill life.\NWhat you can do is block its expression
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.28,0:21:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in this particular form and force it to\Nchoose another form. But you cannot kill
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.67,0:21:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,life. Did you ever chop up a bowl of\Nmercury?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.40,0:21:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's illegal nowadays. You're not\Nallowed to chop up bowls of mercury. But
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.72,0:21:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was a kid, you know, dad would\Nalways bring home mercury. And little
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.15,0:21:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,kids, you know, you try and pick it up.\NAnd of course, it would instant go like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.20,0:21:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that and put a knife down it. No matter\Nwhat you did, you could not break up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.03,0:21:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,this little pool of mercury. It was just\Nmysterious and wonderful. Nowadays, it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.60,0:22:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,probably get you arrested. EPA would be\Naround there ringing your doorbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.84,0:22:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting mercury vapors out into\Nthe world or something. In those days,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.00,0:22:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there was greater freedom and you could\Npoison yourself if you wanted, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.36,0:22:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is there something else you don't\Nhave to worry about? Because as we've
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.08,0:22:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrated before\Nthe time of your death is already set.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.48,0:22:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's reaffirm\Nthe time of birth. The exact time of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.72,0:22:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,your death is already karmically set.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.91,0:22:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The style and manner of it is not set.\NCorrect. The style and the manner of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.15,0:22:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your death is not set. That you have\Nmany choices. But the timing is already
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.36,0:22:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,set.\NWhat can you say about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.55,0:22:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It means you're completely and totally\Nfree. And what is set is the time in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.08,0:23:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically set in which you're going to\Ntrain change form. You're going to come
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.48,0:23:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this form and you're going to go\Ninto a different form where other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.72,0:23:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,choices are awaiting etc. So there's no\Npoint in worrying about what you eat and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,how you eat it and what you do at home\Nbecause when you're going to leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.76,0:23:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to leave here.\NI knew a guy I told you he was his
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.15,0:23:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,father was 92 years old and he's\Nstanding on the street corner in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.60,0:23:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Cottonwood in perfect health. God bless\Nhim. And a cement truck came and smacked
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.08,0:23:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,him and mackerel.\NHe should have kept on drinking the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.08,0:23:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,brandy and smoking cigars and eating the\Nroast beef. You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and his son was saintlike and he said,\N"No, I'm not going to sue the cement
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.44,0:23:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,company." He said, "That that driver\Nfeels terrible." He was reluctant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.60,0:23:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh why should I sue him? I thought that\Nwas very evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.15,0:23:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that he accepted it. Um\Ndoing like God's will and he saw the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.32,0:24:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence of the driver. He said the\Ndriver certainly didn't will that the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.44,0:24:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,last the driver said to him until this\Nmorning I think I'll kill an old man on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.40,0:24:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a street corner. I mean done the other\Nway
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.84,0:24:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,within human error. So our willingness\Nto forgive others for human error is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.48,0:24:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,part of our own salvation. And as the\Nson said that to me I got the feeling of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.96,0:24:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,u his spiritual destiny in a way. This\Nis going to be a saint. I mean he's
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.44,0:24:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,almost a saint already.\NAnd you meet saints in your life, you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.36,0:24:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,know, but it's not popular to think of\Nthem as saints, but um there are uh you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.27,0:24:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,can break down on the highway and a\Ncomplete stranger will do all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.40,0:24:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,things for you, run all over, spend\Nhours in all kinds of trouble. Go get
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.24,0:24:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you a spare tire and drag drag it back\Nand wake his buddy up and who owns the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.24,0:24:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,tire company and brings it back. This is\Nall 4 in the morning. You say, "What
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.91,0:24:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,could this be?"\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.24,0:24:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that. That was\Nan angelic person resist. Yeah. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.12,0:25:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,also have angelics.\NWho would an angel would do a thing like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.03,0:25:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that? And I thought, my god, this this\Nguy is actually an angel in a physical
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.12,0:25:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,body.\NSome kind of a helper angel. He was
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.00,0:25:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God he was an angel in a in a\Nphysical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.79,0:25:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Tell him that\Nlove.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.48,0:25:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You wanted to be killed.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.88,0:25:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Didn't I ever tell him that?\NWell, people ask these extreme
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.48,0:25:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothetical questions, you know, and\Nafter this one, we'll take a quick break
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.60,0:25:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,again. What does an enlightened person\Ndo when a rubber is going to blow you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.44,0:25:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,away?\NSo, I'm going to kill you. What does
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.91,0:25:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened person do? Goes,\Nbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.96,0:25:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind being killed. You know, you\Nshoot out a body and you're in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.24,0:25:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible space. But that loud noise,\Nman, I just hate that loud noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.03,0:25:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's put our fingers in our\Nears and pray for the best and we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.91,0:26:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,meet you again after a short break.\NPeople ask some rather specific
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.64,0:26:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,questions.\NOkay, I need you on this one. We have
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.72,0:26:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,permission to do um this resist. We have\Npermission to do this resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.55,0:26:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.76,0:26:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Most most of the great teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.20,0:26:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of of recent times\Nvery well known some American mostly
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.12,0:26:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they teach in the high they usually get\Nin the high 500s. The ideal level for a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.91,0:26:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher would be\Num the high 500s it would be the perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.60,0:26:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,level.\NFirst of all, lower you don't have
