Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.80,0:42:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And if everybody gets to 540, you've got\Nno worry. I'll tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.80,0:42:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and above, you got no worries with\Nit. That's right. 500 and over, you got
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.56,0:42:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,no worries. uh because that which is\Nloving gravitates into
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.76,0:42:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as it leaves the body that which is\Nuh compatible with that lovingness. It
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.20,0:42:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is not attracted to that which is down\Nthere. It is attracted to beauty. You
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.56,0:42:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,find in your own life as people get more\Nevolved, they tend to seek more and more
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.48,0:42:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,rural areas, less and less noise, less\Nand less activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.48,0:42:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often life comes to a complete\Nstop.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.07,0:42:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says I'm not doing anything\Nin the eyes of the world. And I think
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.56,0:42:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,fantastic\Ncuz that being run by doing this you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.40,0:43:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,know is genulecting at the knee of the\Ndoer within you. The doer is very
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.72,0:43:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,useful. The door will take you out of\Napathy up through the solar plexus into
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.40,0:43:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,rajas into high rajas\Nand then eventually you go into
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.76,0:43:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,tranquility and sattva and at that point\Ndoing this is no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.96,0:43:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a necessity.\NAlso there's the discovery that there is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.28,0:43:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,no doer doing anything. Doing this is\Nhappening of its own. So you neither
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.04,0:43:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,take credit for it nor do you blame\Nyourself for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.20,0:43:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no thinker behind the\Nthinkingness. The thinkingness is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.72,0:43:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking itself.\NThe doingness is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.20,0:43:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the action is activating itself. And you\Nsee that the actions of the body are
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.24,0:43:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,like a karmic windup toy. It's all set\Nto do that. There's no one to take
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.07,0:44:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,credit for it\Nor discredit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.11,0:44:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The illusion that there is, you see,\Nthat's the source of the belief in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.92,0:44:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,causality,\Nthat there is a something, a some
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.00,0:44:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,person, a who\Nthat is secretly controlling all of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.80,0:44:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this. This is the old homunculus sitting\Nin the back of your brain pulling all
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.48,0:44:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the switches.\NThere is an operations center within the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.48,0:44:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ego\Nthat integrates an enormously complex
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.56,0:44:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,series of functions and I talk about it\NI forget I the eye or I I forget which
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.00,0:44:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there is this operations center where\Nwhen you look at what the human mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.68,0:44:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,asked to do it's no computer could come\Nanywhere near it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.04,0:44:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of multiple options decided you\Num chosen and pathways from instant to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.11,0:44:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,instant all within a feeling is complex\Nbecause all decisions, thoughts and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.20,0:45:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,feelings are also filed in the memory\Nfile according to feeling tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.92,0:45:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The complexity is mind-boggling.\NTogether with unconscious factors,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.96,0:45:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,together with energies within the field\Nof which you have no knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.35,0:45:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,together with enormous uh complexity of\Nprograms coming from past karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.40,0:45:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,momentum,\Nno computer could even get near it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.68,0:45:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't could not get near it because\Nit's not within the realm of logic
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.92,0:45:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because the entire field shifts every\Ntime context shifts in the slightest.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.52,0:45:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole field shifts and nothing that\Nyou're even into is even applicable. The
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.68,0:45:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,minute the field shifts a little bit,\Nit's all nonsensical.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.44,0:45:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the purpose of humor.\NUh never trust anybody who doesn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.16,0:45:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a sense of humor. They're dangerous.\NThey're killers.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.83,0:45:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All killers are humorless.\NWe just stepped on a scorpion in the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.88,0:45:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,back. We were talking about is there\Ndeath? There was this big scorpion which
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.83,0:46:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,now to me was not integrous because if\Nyou get a scorpion sting on the tail it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.52,0:46:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,can be fatal. You know what I'm saying?\NOkay,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.76,0:46:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that was integrous. Uh, the scorpion is\Ndead.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.88,0:46:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This scorpion is dead. Scorpioness is\Ndead. Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.11,0:46:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I get what it was. All right. Okay. It\Ncame right out of the lecture, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.11,0:46:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAll right. So
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.59,0:46:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the decisions that we make uh the\Nintention behind them is what sets the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.88,0:46:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic energy fuel going.\NThe same action out of revenge or hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.35,0:46:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,uh has a different uh karmic consequence\Nthan let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.31,0:46:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect one's integrity. To kill out\Nof anger, fear, revenge or greed is a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.04,0:47:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,totally different act\Nthan defending one's homeland, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.11,0:47:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,say, which you have no no choice. You\Nhave a wife and a family and children.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.83,0:47:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Huns are coming over the horizon\Nwith their sims flashing and u
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.24,0:47:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they always they always kill everybody\Nthey conquer. That was tradition in the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.00,0:47:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,great hordes of history. They always\Nkilled everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.76,0:47:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You massacred all of them and you took\Nthe loot.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.20,0:47:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why slavery was an advance in\Nconsciousness because suddenly humans
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.88,0:47:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,had a value. Hey, we won't kill them,\Nwe'll sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.11,0:47:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether slavery is one way or slavery\Nis the other depends on which direction
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.40,0:47:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you look at it.\NAnd as we said in the last lecture, a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.72,0:47:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,slave in in the south of America lived\Nto be 56 years old. And a slave left in
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.04,0:48:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the wild of Africa where the fellow\Ntribes would kill you probably lived
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.56,0:48:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about age 28.\NSo your life was preserved. You got
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.44,0:48:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,medical help. You got nutrition. You got\Nclothing. You got food. You got the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.72,0:48:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,necessities of life instead of being\Nmassacred. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.68,0:48:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how everything is shifts\Ndepending on perception. Whether you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.76,0:48:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,shift to the past and look at it towards\Nthe future or project yourself in the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.16,0:48:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,future and look back at the past that's\Nwhy to save the world you talk you know
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.40,0:48:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when Ramana Maharashi is saying is that\Nall you could be working on is your
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.44,0:48:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion about your own perceptions\Nthat no such thing exists is an advance
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.31,0:48:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it a cruelty depends on how you\Nlook at
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.04,0:48:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a slave on a slave ship on a\Ngalley in a state of advanced agony
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.40,0:48:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,was what? Horrible.\NYeah, horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.68,0:49:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then was taking the great chance\NI could leave the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.07,0:49:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure there was a spirit.\NI had to let go that which is known. I
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.76,0:49:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,am a physicality with the intuitive\Nsuggestion. It was an intuition that one
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.59,0:49:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is a spirit\Nfree as a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.64,0:49:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So was being chained to a galley a\Nhorrible event or was it a the doorway
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.11,0:49:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to enlightenment? Because that was the\Nfirst lifetime of discovery in conscious
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.04,0:49:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,memory that one is actually a spirit.\Nthat that which I am rose up out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.44,0:49:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,phys physicality.\NThey had to drag it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.72,0:49:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sirism, right?\NSo behind that which you think is um a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.76,0:50:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,thinker, a thinking is a thinker. There\Nis no thinker there. So you don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.68,0:50:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to worry about the thinker because there\Nisn't any. You just look at the thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.44,0:50:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NAnd we try to transcend the blocks to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.55,0:50:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment by understanding the\Nnature of the construction of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.04,0:50:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we've handled most of these now\Nand therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.68,0:50:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> okay I thought we'd finish some other\Nthings I wanted to say. Okay. Is there
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.16,0:50:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,more questions before we go on?\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.72,0:50:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,language say I go from here to here.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, this is something we have\Naddressed in previous lectures and we
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.59,0:50:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have addressed quite a bit in the books.\NA lot of a lot of attention given to in
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.96,0:50:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the books.\NHow the ego comes into being and how it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.04,0:51:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,gains its structure.\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.20,0:51:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego cannot discern the difference\Nbetween the an abstract concept and
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.72,0:51:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.\NThat's why an abstract concept is one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.64,0:51:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thing.\NIt doesn't have any real concordant
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.96,0:51:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. That's really a parallel\Nconfirmation. Doesn't really this does
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.00,0:51:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not flow into this. This flows parallel\Nto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.31,0:51:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the question\N>> that in my perception I'm causing this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.96,0:51:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,paper?\N>> Oh yes. Yes. Causality. Yes. That
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.83,0:51:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,question about has come up before. So we\Nshould go more into causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.16,0:51:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The the the mind thinks in terms of\Nabstractions
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.68,0:51:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then thinks that if it can be\Nnominalized
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.68,0:52:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,given a word a name therefore it has\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.64,0:52:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We can call things transformation.\NWe can we can call them all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.80,0:52:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,things.\NIs such a thing happening in reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.44,0:52:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's happening in my mind.\NThis is an abstract
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.20,0:52:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,conceptualization.\NOne of the most difficult things about
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.92,0:52:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,transcending the mind is\Ntranscending the belief that concepts
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.31,0:52:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,um represent\Num an an independent reality, some kind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.59,0:52:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of an objective reality.\NIf you go out there, no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.52,0:52:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,exists out there. Doesn't exist. You can\Nlook all over the world
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.92,0:52:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and never find causality\Nbecause causality exists only as an
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.72,0:52:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,abstract concept in your head.\NYou'll just keep projecting that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.64,0:53:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,abstract concept over and over again\Nto everything you see. All that means is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.88,0:53:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you're projecting that thought, that\Nargument, that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.64,0:53:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,concept onto the world over and over\Nagain.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.44,0:53:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was younger, I always had a hard\Ntime
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.72,0:53:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with homesickness and leaving any place.\NAnd I would mourn it. Even if I lived in
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.44,0:53:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a cardboard box under a bridge that said\NKleenex on it, camp out there for a
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.92,0:53:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of weeks, I would mourn it.\NI really missed my big Kleenex box. Had
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.20,0:53:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,everything arranged in there just the\Nway I wanted it with the little windows
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.59,0:53:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and cardboard and all, you know.\NI had a stone fort as a kid. Then they
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.07,0:53:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,came along and moved all the stones.\NThey're going to make something with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.48,0:53:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\NI always got attached to wherever I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.48,0:53:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,lived.\NHome. It was home. Home is where the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.80,0:53:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,heart is. So, my heart would be wherever\NI lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.96,0:54:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in the depths of uh not having money,\Nwhich is the kind you could call poverty
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.16,0:54:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,nowadays, I suppose.\NIn the depths of not really having any
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.96,0:54:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,cash, you could live in some rather\Nmiserable places. And then when you left
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.31,0:54:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,them, grieve all over again with\Nhomesickness for a little one and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.96,0:54:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,room up on the roof of somebody's house.\NThat
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.07,0:54:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so it was so painful. It took me a long\Ntime to like it was just like
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.00,0:54:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,homesickness. If you ever been homesick,\Nyou know that feeling. So I learned that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.24,0:54:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that was painful. So if I moved, I would\Nrent a new place and I would pay the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.31,0:54:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,rent on the old place\Nso that I could move back there if I
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.35,0:54:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't stand this homesickness. Paid\Nrent on two places.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.96,0:54:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If in a couple of months I couldn't\Nstand it, I could always move back
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.76,0:54:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,there. the knowingness that I could move\Nback if I wanted ease the pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.31,0:55:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This happened over and over again. Every\Nplace I left, I would go through this
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.11,0:55:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,pain of loss, heartbreak, like losing a\Nlover,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.52,0:55:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nyou know, it was the homesickness of the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.04,0:55:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,child for instance. So home was a very\Nvery special place.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.48,0:55:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And one time here I am leaving this huge\Nestate you know which was really
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.35,0:55:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,spectacular really showplace\Nand as I leave that I realize I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.44,0:55:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to project that sense of at homeness\Nonto the next place I go it's in me not
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.04,0:55:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in it.\NEach place I lived I projected the sense
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.92,0:55:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of home safety love familiarity.\NIt came from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.80,0:55:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it all over again the rest of my\Nlife. If I have to move from where I I
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.40,0:55:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,am now, the next place will become\Nspecial all over again. Right? Soon as
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.04,0:55:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you move in, you fix it all up and now\Nit's special.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.48,0:56:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Got the magic touch of yourself there.\NSo this the feeling of being at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.31,0:56:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,comfort, secure, and all that goes with\Nhomelessness which derives from
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.83,0:56:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,childhood got projected onto every place\Nthat you live. You project it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.55,0:56:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not there.\NIf we take a microscope and we take a
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.72,0:56:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whatchamacallit meter and take every\Nmolecule of that home apart, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.96,0:56:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not find feeling at homeness there.\NThat's from here. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.88,0:56:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with causality.\NEverything you see because you see
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.76,0:56:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sequence in the world, you then your\Nmind jumps in and projects the concept
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.96,0:56:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,causality.\NThis is causing that. This is causing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.79,0:56:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that. In reality, what you see is the\Nsequence of perception
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.11,0:56:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as this, you know, creation unfolds\Nitself this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.31,0:57:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.52,0:57:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is nothing causing the hand to\Nunfold.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.92,0:57:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It has innate within it potentiality.\NThen a person says,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.35,0:57:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yes, but isn't there an eye causing it\Nby intention?"
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.28,0:57:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Today's lecture has to do with how to\Ntranscend duality. That is duality
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.79,0:57:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,per se, that there is an eye causing an\Nit through some magical modality called
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.31,0:57:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,causality. And that is the trap of the\Nmind to believe in the reality of any of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.92,0:57:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,these three factors. First of all,\Nthere's nothing happening out there. Nor
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.16,0:57:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is there causality. Nor is there any\Nintrinsic independent entity called I to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.79,0:57:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,be causing it. H all things come into\Nbeing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.07,0:58:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by the unfoldment of the potentiality of\Ncreation. And as it is witnessed
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.76,0:58:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sequentially to perception, one one\Nthinks that this is causing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.48,0:58:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take that one point of\Nobservation out of time and space, then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.59,0:58:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no sequence to which you would\Nbe ascribing the magical quality called
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.28,0:58:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,causality.\NIf we back up the movie and you see the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.96,0:58:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,lady running backwards, you say, "What's\Ncausing her to run backwards?" Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.40,0:58:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,she's not running backwards.\NIt's only perception. You see,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.59,0:58:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that the concept happening in\Nitself is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.79,0:58:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing happening.\NThere's nothing happening now.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.52,0:58:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing happening now.\NSomething didn't happen a minute ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.88,0:58:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is not about to happen now\Neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.20,0:59:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NAll right. You have perception
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.28,0:59:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,arbitrarily. I could say we start now\Nand we end now. That's a happening. Or I
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.83,0:59:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,could say no. We'll start now and we'll\Nkeep going there. No, that's a
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.72,0:59:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,happening. We could start 9:00 this\Nmorning till 4:00 this this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.59,0:59:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, that's a 7-hour happening. Well,\Nwe could start from 9 to 9:01. That was
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.20,0:59:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a happening.\NThat was happening. Did you catch it? Is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.72,0:59:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,your camera ready? Happening. Happening.\NNow that was a happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.35,0:59:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yokoono used to specialize in\Nhappenings.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.92,1:00:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a bonfire that would go off with rockets\Nat midnight on
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.11,1:00:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in these village somewhere. H\Nshe chose to start it there and end it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.35,1:00:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,there. No, I say the happening was when\Nyou set up the bonfire stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.31,1:00:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the happening continued until after\Nthe police left.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.04,1:00:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a happening.\NNow policeman would say it began to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.52,1:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,happen after she ran his bonfire. We got\Nthere, caught her hand red-handed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.00,1:00:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the start of the happening to\Nhim. Then we took him off to jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.28,1:00:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the end of the happening. And I\Nbooked her. That's the end of the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.44,1:00:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,happening\Nto the lawyer. That's only the start of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.79,1:00:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the happening. She got taken out of\Njail. It's a violation of her civil
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.52,1:00:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,rights. No, no, it started from there\Nand it's going on till right now. And I
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.83,1:00:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,will defend her in court. She was only\Nexpressing this the first amendment
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.55,1:00:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,expressing our freedom to create.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.64,1:01:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We project then this onto the world and\Nsay it's out there whereas it's in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.28,1:01:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?\NThere is no happening anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.40,1:01:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no I person causing the\Nhappening.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.40,1:01:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no causality to account for it.\NThis arm has the potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.59,1:01:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to do that.\NLet's say if I choose a pattern off of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.96,1:01:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite number of patterns. If I\Nchoose this pattern, this automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.64,1:01:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,does this. If I choose this pattern, the\Nomega does this. If I choose this
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.44,1:02:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,pattern, it does this.\NA great moment in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.24,1:02:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So by choice we release certain\Npotentialities by choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.96,1:02:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see within the seed is the whole\Nprogram
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.48,1:02:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of it defining its potentiality in terms\Nof nonlinear potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.24,1:02:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,See, causality is looking within the\NNewtonian linear domain which always
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.04,1:02:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sees a happening with a beginning, a\Ncause and an end, a consequence, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.00,1:02:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very limited paradigm of\Nreality.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.44,1:02:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't take you to the dimensions that\Nyou go to because the minute you get
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.07,1:02:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond logic, the 400s, these things are\Nnot even valid questions anymore. Once
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.04,1:02:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to the 500s and you're talking\Nabout love, you're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.92,1:02:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,quality. Now it's not measurable.\NDoesn't start here and end there. Can't
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.52,1:03:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,package it. There's any love meter.\NIt's beyond definition
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.96,1:03:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,by logic.\NThe person says, "Yes, but I want love
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.83,1:03:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to fit into the comfortable box of\Nthinkingness and logic."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.31,1:03:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we make feudal attempts. Poetry\Nprobably gets the closest. How do I love
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.28,1:03:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,thee? Let me count the ways.\NAs a kid, I thought, boy, boys don't
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.07,1:03:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,like poetry.\NHow do I love the Let me count the ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.52,1:03:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break. You know,\N8-year-old boy just loathe that kind of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.88,1:03:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff, you know.\NSo, that which is seen as beautiful and
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.48,1:03:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness is the turnoff. Every\N8-year-old says, "Waffle shit." Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.92,1:03:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,women and girls like that crap. You know\Nwhat I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.96,1:03:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,See, so it doesn't even have any\Nreality. See, it doesn't have any
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.24,1:03:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. Or he'd be forced to accept\Nthat it's beautiful and loving. No, he
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.07,1:04:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,has choice. All right? So the minute we\Nget beyond the confines of logic, which
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.44,1:04:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on definition.\NWe're in a different domain. So what
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.55,1:04:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we're doing here is stretching\Nepistemology. Another one of the ways to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.76,1:04:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God is to follow epistemology to its\Nfinal
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.28,1:04:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ferocious end. And you crash through\Nfrom epistemology. How do we know? And
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.68,1:04:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,how do we know that we know?\NYou make a concept called causality. How
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.24,1:04:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,do you know that you know what causality\Neven is? It's just a word. It's just a
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.76,1:04:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,tautology. Well, cause is anything you\Nwant to call it, isn't it? It's just t a
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.83,1:04:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,u t\Nthe string is taught now
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.11,1:04:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,cause is anything you want to call it.\NYou can say love is the cause of these
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.83,1:04:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,people behaving this way. Not the cause.\NIt's the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.52,1:05:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in that field that you're making\Ncertain choices
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.59,1:05:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that are really answerable in a way to\Nthe field of love because that now is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.24,1:05:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the context of truth and value. Outside\Nof love, the world of business, we were
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.24,1:05:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about it during the break.\NBusiness doesn't give a diddly about
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.16,1:05:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,love.\NYou're not even allowed to engage in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.31,1:05:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,love during lunch breaks,\Nmuch less on the premises, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.31,1:05:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Touchyfey\Nis not, you know, cool in the business
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.48,1:05:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,world. Being cool and logical is cool in\Nthe business world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.00,1:05:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right? So, the minute you get out of\Nthe dimension, then we need our scale of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.03,1:05:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness again. The minute we get\Nout of the 400s, then
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.03,1:05:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,causality becomes less and less\Nmeaningful.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.03,1:05:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean up here? It doesn't\Nmean anything in the field of love and
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.79,1:06:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,joy and peace.\NIt doesn't even come up as a credible
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.59,1:06:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility.\NNothing is causing you to feel peace
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.72,1:06:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in this room. There's absolute silence.\NBehind all the noise
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.52,1:06:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,there's absolute silence. Remove the\Nnoise and then linger with silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.79,1:06:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct?\NNothing is causing the silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.48,1:06:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing your existence.\NEverything is by free choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.40,1:06:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest comes the\Nmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.44,1:06:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that all things are created\Nwith the one single essential quality of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.68,1:06:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NWithin that existence
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.48,1:06:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,combined with form you have an infinite\Nseries of potentialities.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.96,1:07:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing it to happen.\NSo if we put a seedling, a rose seedling
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.11,1:07:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the sun and give it water and\Nfertilizer, the sun and the water and
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.76,1:07:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the fertilizer do not cause it to grow.\NThe
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.16,1:07:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,seed does not cause it to grow. Doesn't\Ncause it. Cause you see is really within
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.68,1:07:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of force. The world of power\Nhere is different. From 200 down, we
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.31,1:07:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have the world of force in which one\Nthing forces something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.52,1:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not cause. That's force.\NCause you'd have to be divine. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.44,1:07:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,These things are manifesting.\NThe choice of that as a potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.35,1:07:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,built within the human is the capacity\Nto begin to vibrate at the energy of the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.55,1:08:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,kitty's purr, the doggy's wagging tail.\NAnd those are often the first things we
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.79,1:08:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,love. That's why we give children pets\Nand the toys and the fuzzy warm things
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.79,1:08:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because they begin to grasp their\Ncapacity to lovingness. And then they
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.48,1:08:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,get attached to that which are they're\Nloving and they grieve and go into loss.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.88,1:08:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they learn that they can\Nrecreate the same feeling about the next
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.31,1:08:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,toy. And then they've transcended the\Nattachment to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.67,1:08:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The attachment to love which also\Nbecomes a block. And we'll talk about
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.52,1:08:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that more or less next time.\NI just want you to see that causality is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.04,1:08:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,an illusion,\Na powerful illusion. It's the whole it's
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.71,1:08:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole basis of the ego. That's why\Nit's so powerful and why it takes a lot
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.60,1:08:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of prayer and\Ninner spiritual work to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.71,1:09:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden you see that everything\Nis happening of its own. Nothing is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.83,1:09:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,causing anything to happen. The world of\Nphenomena, the universe of creation is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.96,1:09:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,like a giant electromagnetic field. All\Nthings within it have a certain charge,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.35,1:09:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain energy, a certain polarity.\Nlike little iron fail filings with a
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.44,1:09:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,north pole and a south pole and a\Ncertain spin and a certain degree of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.04,1:09:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,magn magnetic energy composed of various\Nelements
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.92,1:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and where it is in the space with\Nbillions and billions of others
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.00,1:09:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically allows it to move within\Nthe realm of possibilities like the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.04,1:09:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,aurora borealis you see the aurora\Nborealis is nobody's causing it to do
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.44,1:09:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's\NThe poles of the earth send out that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.56,1:09:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,electromagnetic. And you see everybody's\Nhere seen the Aurora Borealis.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.48,1:10:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how they are they dance the\Npattern dances itself spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.36,1:10:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as an interaction between that which it\Nis and the universe in which it is
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.08,1:10:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,located. Nothing is causing anything to\Nhappen.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.84,1:10:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,H we spend some time on causality\Nbecause it is so intrinsic to the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.04,1:10:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,structure of the ego.\NTo merely begin to question causality as
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.23,1:10:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of an intrinsic reality\Nalready weakens its power and holding
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.40,1:10:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego together.\NIt already it's already weakened just by
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.28,1:10:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,questioning\Nits authenticity. It has no objective
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.76,1:10:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,substantial substantial reality of its\Nown. The only reality that can be
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.60,1:10:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,confirmed is a subjective state called\NI. The presence of God within oneself.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.44,1:10:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The self with a capital S which\Nilluminates itself into your awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.96,1:11:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as the feeling is that there there is an\NI and that I exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.56,1:11:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only reality you actually\Nknow.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.08,1:11:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that is all imagination\Nother than that you exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.04,1:11:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no confirmable knowledge that\Nyou can possibly hold.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.40,1:11:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything else then is a hypothetical\Npossibility. Everything piece of data
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.44,1:11:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind holds is a hypothetical\Nabstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.80,1:11:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The only verification of reality then is\Nthe state of subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.48,1:11:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The only radically objective truth then\Nis subjectivity itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.04,1:11:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the subjective, no objective\Ncould be said to exist. Because what
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.60,1:11:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,would say that it exists?\NOnly the subjective sense of self says
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.88,1:12:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an objective reality is out there.\NAll conclusions, all mentations and are
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.52,1:12:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,distilled down to a radical sense of\Nsubjectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.08,1:12:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the only reality\Nthat can exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.04,1:12:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God within\Nshines forth as
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.08,1:12:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,self that which I am\Nand that's the only thing you know is
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.04,1:12:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that you exist.\NAll the rest is software put on top of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.04,1:12:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,your hardware\Nother than the fact that you exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.28,1:12:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else is really knowable.\NAnd all the great imaginations that all
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.23,1:12:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the great eagles through all time have\Narrived at calibrate the great books of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.40,1:12:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the western world, all the greatest\Nthinkers of all time which I have in a
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.60,1:12:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,library at home. Is it the greatest\Nthinkers of all time lined up from
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.64,1:13:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,ancient Greece? The last one on the\Nseries I think is called Freud
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.00,1:13:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and they calibrated 475.\NThe greatest thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.84,1:13:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the history of the world calibrates\Nat 475.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.28,1:13:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest geniuses that have ever\Nlived, Einstein and Newton, are 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.15,1:13:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking for a reality that's in\Nthe 500s and up.
